	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=5595&mid=106380913371686>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=5595&mid=106380913371686>New use for Wind</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=5595&mid=106380913371686#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Sep 17th 10:35 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=133653><span id=Scholar>cujomatic</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>35 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The value of wind has increased a bit with the LoY/PoP/LDoN expansions.<br><br>Wind bonus affects how many disease/curse counters are removed by the 44/52 LoY Aria songs.<br><br>Having said that, its important to at least equip a basic wind, 1.8 mod minimum, vs the 1.0 singing mod. The difference between 1.8 and the 2.1 on this flute is less dramatic.<br><br>In LDoN, where traps can affect the whole party, it can be helpful for the bard to help memove the disease/curse. Plus, these songs probably have the coolest graphics (pacman anyone?) we get from a song....a lot of fun at parties.</p>&nbsp;<br>Baron Nesoohc Tsal, the Rathe<br>Bard of the 65th Verse<br>(alts Fixem 52 Cleric Fletchum 51 Ranger, The Rathe<br>Bhandade 52th season Cleric, Krescendo, 52th Bard, Firiona Vie)</td></tr>
